## Overview

This project is a modern, production-ready Python package scaffolded from an opinionated Copier template. It uses a high-performance technology stack designed for developer productivity and robust code quality.

- **CLI Framework**: Typer
- **Package Management**: uv
- **Code Quality**: ruff, mypy, bandit
- **Testing**: pytest with coverage
- **Build System**: setuptools
- **CI/CD**: GitHub Actions

## Developer Experience

This project includes a `Makefile` to streamline common development tasks.

| Command | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `make install` | Creates a virtual environment and installs all project dependencies. |
| `make lint` | Formats the code and runs the linter using ruff. |
| `make test` | Executes the test suite with pytest and generates a coverage report. |
| `make security` | Scans the codebase for security vulnerabilities using bandit. |
| `make check-all` | Sequentially runs the lint, test, and security checks. |
| `make run` | Runs the CLI application (pass args with `ARGS="--name Alice"`). |
| `make build` | Builds the source distribution (sdist) and wheel. |
| `make publish` | Builds and publishes the package to PyPI. |

## Getting Started

Install dependencies:

```bash
make install
```

Run the CLI:

```bash
make run ARGS="--name World"
```

Run quality checks:

```bash
make check-all
```
